    <div class="container">
        <a href="blog.html">← Journal</a>
        
        <h1>FIRST PRINCIPLES</h1>
        <span class="meta">ENTRY 001 /// GEOMETRY</span>

        <p>Most youth coaches start the season with a formation. They draw a "2-3-1" or a "3-2-1" on a whiteboard and tell seven-year-olds where to stand. This is the first mistake.</p>

        <p>At <strong>Soccerates</strong>, we don't look at the "what" (the formation). We look at the "why" (the physics). If you strip away the jerseys and the grass, 7v7 soccer is simply a problem of <strong>Resource Allocation</strong>.</p>

        <div class="math-box">
            EFFICIENCY = SPACE (S) / TIME (T)
        </div>

        <h2>The Diamond is a Tool</h2>
        <p>We teach the "Diamond" shape in 7v7 not because it looks nice, but because it mathematically stretches the opponent’s time (T). When our center-back has the ball and our two defenders split wide to the touchlines, we increase the Space (S) the opponent must defend.</p>

        <p>Stop shouting "Get back in position!" Start asking: <em>"How can you create more time for your teammate?"</em></p>
    </div>
</body>
